{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17537445","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17537445"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:17:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:17:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16029"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16029"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.34,0.11,0.27,0.2]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8720"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108846"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8720","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8720"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16029"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91210"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"92"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4984"},{"type":"tags","id":"8976"},{"type":"tags","id":"9051"},{"type":"tags","id":"9270"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20851"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41782"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108846"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a five-day history of painful, swollen joints and an itchy rash. She also reports dark urine and yellowing of her eyes for the past two days. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She returned two months ago from backpacking in Southeast Asia for six months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears unwell. Her pulse rate is 88/min, blood pressure 118/74 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.6\u00b0C. She has scleral icterus and a widespread urticarial rash with macules and petechial lesions. There is symmetrical swelling and tenderness of her wrists and knees. Her abdomen is soft with mild right upper quadrant tenderness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBilirubin 85 \u00b5mol/L (3-20)\u003Cbr /\u003EALT 850 U/L (5-40)\u003Cbr /\u003EAST 920 U/L (5-40)\u003Cbr /\u003EALP 180 U/L (30-110)\u003Cbr /\u003EAlbumin 38 g/L (35-50)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Drug-induced hepatitis","Hepatitis B infection","Hepatitis C infection","Leptospirosis","Autoimmune hepatitis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with the classic serum sickness-like prodrome of acute viral hepatitis, characterised by urticaria and arthralgia, followed by jaundice. The urticaria is often pruritic. The pattern of liver enzyme derangement shows a predominantly hepatocellular pattern with marked transaminitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis B infection\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely diagnosis given the characteristic presentation of serum sickness-like prodrome (urticaria and arthralgia) followed by jaundice. This presentation occurs in 20 - 30% of acute hepatitis B infections and is thought to be due to circulating immune complexes during the early phase of infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDrug-induced hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E can present with jaundice and elevated liver enzymes, but typically lacks the characteristic serum sickness-like prodrome with urticaria and arthralgia seen in this case. Additionally, there is no history of medication use that might trigger this reaction. While some drugs can cause a hypersensitivity reaction with rash and fever, the combination of symptoms and travel history makes viral hepatitis more likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis C infection\u003C/strong\u003E is usually asymptomatic in its acute phase and rarely causes jaundice or systemic symptoms. When symptomatic, it does not typically cause the serum sickness-like prodrome seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeptospirosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a zoonotic disease that can be acquired during travel to Southeast Asia and can cause hepatitis. However, it typically presents with biphasic illness with initial fever, headache, and myalgia followed by a second phase that may include jaundice. The characteristic urticarial rash and arthralgia seen in this patient are not typical features of leptospirosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAutoimmune hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E can present with arthralgia and may have associated skin manifestations, but these are typically in the form of other autoimmune phenomena such as vitiligo or lupus-like rashes rather than urticaria. The acute presentation and recent travel history make viral hepatitis more likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s worth noting that Hepatitis A can also occasionally present with urticaria and arthralgia, though less commonly than Hepatitis B. The diagnosis would be confirmed with hepatitis B serology, including hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) and IgM anti-core antibody (anti-HBc IgM). Most cases of acute hepatitis B are self-limiting, but patients should be monitored for progression to fulminant hepatitis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Hepatitis B infection commonly presents with a serum sickness-like prodrome of urticaria and arthralgia before the onset of jaundice.","The presence of urticaria and arthralgia helps distinguish viral hepatitis from other causes of acute jaundice.","Travel history and clinical presentation are key factors in differentiating between various causes of acute hepatitis."],"references":["Kappus MR, Sterling RK. Extrahepatic manifestations of acute hepatitis B virus infection. Gastroenterology Hepatology.  2013.  Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3754772/","Turnbull N, Mitchell G.  Skin signs of viral hepatitis. DermNet NZ.  2021.  Available at: https://dermnetnz.org/topics/skin-signs-of-viral-hepatitis"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91210"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16029"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91210","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/91210"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-13T18:52:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-01T20:04:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8720"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108846"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"